OL,3,CUniversity contributed to death of
OL,4,Cstudent who took her own life, court
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,F"Their arguments that they did not
OL,8,Fknow enough about Natasha's problems,
OL,9,For that they hadn't received the right
OL,10,Fpaperwork, or that fairness to other
OL,11,Fstudents meant they couldn't make the
OL,12,Fadjustments she needed, have now all
OL,13,Ffailed for a second time.
OL,15,F"It is now for the University of
OL,16,FBristol, and higher education
OL,17,Finstitutions across the country, to
OL,18,Fget their houses in order."
