OL,3,CUniversity contributed to death of
OL,4,Cstudent who took her own life, court
OL,5,Cfinds
OL,7,F"In appealing, we were seeking clarity
OL,8,Ffor the Higher Education sector around
OL,9,Fthe application of the Equality Act
OL,10,Fwhen staff do not know a student has a
OL,11,Fdisability, or when it has yet to be
OL,12,Fdiagnosed. We will work with
OL,13,Fcolleagues across the sector as we
OL,14,Fconsider the judgment.
OL,16,F"I am grateful to our dedicated
OL,17,Fcolleagues who work tirelessly to
OL,18,Fsupport all our students and to those
OL,19,Fwho specifically supported Natasha
OL,20,Fwhich included a referral to the NHS.
